.TH man 1 "APRIL 2023" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple shell created in C to interact with a linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
 hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell is a UNIX term for the interactive user interface with an operating system. The shell is the layer of programming that understands
and executes the commands a user enters. In some systems, the shell is called a command interpreter. A shell usually implies an interface
with a command syntax 

.B Overview

The Simple shell just like the UNIX shell is a command-line interpreter or shell that provides a command line user interface for operating systems. The shell is both an interactive command language and a scripting language, and is used by the operating system to control the execution of the system using shell scripts.
.SH Return Value

Always 0 for success, other number means failure.

.SH PATH

It will look inside all directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options will be typed after the main command followed by a space and a
 '-' symbol.


.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

.SH BUGS
Single space required after argument.


